<br>
1) Who is the most powerful military in the world?<br>
2) Who is the number one economy in the world? <br>
3) Who has put more military in UN missions on average by at least 2/3rds? <br>
4) Who, if their economy was removed from the world, would drop the worlds GDP by over 20%? <br>
5) Who do most people in the world get their military weapons from? and as follow up:<br>
6) What would happen to the military technology of the world if we stopped sharing it with others? Would it fall dramatically behind us even further?<br>
7) Who provides more of the humanitarian aid around the world then any other country by a large degree?<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  What would happen if the U.S. stopped providing humanitarian aid to other nations? <br>
<br>
So, until you all can pick up that tab and make the rest of the world not so dependent on us it doesnt matter if we are wrong or right because YOU CANT CHANGE ANYTHING until you stop all that from being true. <br>
<br>
Of course, you will change the argument again without being able to simply admit one thing. That what I say is true.  Because once you admit its true, then you realize that the only way to fix it is to not be dependent on us. Then you must ask yourself how the world can do that, and you will find it next to impossible. Therefore, you will just be able to go back to whining and bitching because there is nothing you can do to change it. <br>
<br>
I believe we are right, you believe we are wrong. We have the ability to back up our stance untouched, you do not.  Your stance, if we are proven victorious and correct, can lead to France's further degradation of power in the world view. <br>
<br>
Bigger risk for you, less of a risk for us. If we are wrong, we beat the @#%$ out of George Bush in the next election and get a bunch of liberatarians and democrats taking a bunch of seats, and the Republicans get punished for it.  Things get better for us again.  If we are right, more Republicans take seats and continue to push the U.S. into the new world order. <br>
<br>
BTW, I still call them French Fries. I have not run into a single place calling them Freedom Fries.  Because some stupid state government official got a wild hair up his ass to get attention, doesnt mean its a shared philosophy.  However, it is fun to offer angryfrenchman01's a freedom fry on the net... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-size:x-large;"> V</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-size:medium;">irest</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-size:x-large;">T</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-size:medium;">ael</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-size:x-large;">W</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-size:medium;">aggler</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
